claimForSpecificWalletId(address,uint256.details: If for a specific walletId, the tokens could not be transferred for some reason, it will added to the unclaimableAmounts      of the paymentReceiver, and the amount would no longer hold any co-relation with the specific walletId of the paymentReceiver.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClient} instance address that processes the walletId claim from _msgSender

params.walletId: The ID of the payment order for which claim is being made
Id of the wallet for which dueTo is fetched

identifier().details: The identifier is defined as the keccak256 hash of the module's      abi packed encoded major version, url and title.

init(address,(uint256,uint256,string,str.details: CAN be overriden by downstream contract.MUST call `__Module_init()`.

params.configData: Variable config data for specific module                   implementations.

isActivePaymentReceiver(address,address).details: this function is for convenience and can be easily figured out by other means in the codebase.

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: We imitate here the EIP2771 Standard to enable metatransactions As it currently stands we dont want to feed the forwarder address to each module individually and we decided to move this to the orchestrator

params.forwarder: The contract address to be verified.

returns._0: bool Is the given address the trusted forwarder

processPayments(address).details: It's up to the the implementation to keep up with what has been      paid out or not.

params.walletId: Id of the wallet for which the releasable amount is fetched
Id of the wallet for which released is fetched

removeAllPaymentReceiverPayments(address.details: this function calls _removePayment which goes through all the payment orders for a paymentReceiver. For the payment orders      that are completely vested, their details are deleted in the _claimForSpecificWalletId function and for others it is      deleted in the _removePayment function only, leaving the unvested tokens as balance of the paymentClient itself.

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClient} instance address from which we will remove the payments

removePaymentForSpecificWalletId(address.details: the detail of the wallet that is being removed is either deleted in the _claimForSpecificWalletId or later down in this      function itself depending on the timestamp of when this function was called

params.client: The {IERC20PaymentClient} instance address from which we will remove the payment
params.paymentReceiver: address of the paymentReceiver whose payment order is to be removed
params.retryForUnclaimableAmounts: boolean that determines whether the function would try to return the unclaimableAmounts along        with the vested amounts from the payment order with id = walletId to the paymentReceiver
params.walletId: The ID of the paymentReceiver's payment order which is to be removed
Id of the wallet for which start is fetched

params.timestamp: the time upto which we want the vested amount

cancelRunningPayments(address).notice: Cancels all unfinished payments from an {IERC20PaymentClient} instance.

claimAll(address).notice: claim everything that the paymentClient owes to the _msgSender till the current timestamp

claimForSpecificWalletId(address,uint256.notice: claim the salary uptil block.timestamp from the client for a payment order with id = walletId by _msgSender

dueToForSpecificWalletId(address,address.notice: Getter for the vesting dueTo timestamp of a particular payment order with id = walletId associated with a particular paymentReceiver

isActivePaymentReceiver(address,address).notice: tells whether a paymentReceiver has any pending payments for a particular client

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: Checks if the provided address is the trusted forwarder

numVestingWallets(address,address).notice: provides a unique id for new payment orders added for a specific client & paymentReceiver combo

processPayments(address).notice: Processes all payments from an {IERC20PaymentClient} instance.

releasableForSpecificWalletId(address,ad.notice: Getter for the amount of releasable tokens for a particular payment order with id = walletId associated with a particular paymentReceiver.

releasedForSpecificWalletId(address,addr.notice: Getter for the amount of tokens already released for a particular payment order with id = walletId associated with a particular paymentReceiver

removeAllPaymentReceiverPayments(address.notice: Deletes all payments related to a paymentReceiver & leaves unvested tokens in the ERC20PaymentClient.

removePaymentForSpecificWalletId(address.notice: Deletes a specific payment with id = walletId for a paymentReceiver & leaves unvested tokens in the ERC20PaymentClient.

startForSpecificWalletId(address,address.notice: Getter for the start timestamp of a particular payment order with id = walletId associated with a particular paymentReceiver

token().notice: Returns the IERC20 token the payment processor can process.

unclaimable(address,address).notice: Getter for the amount of tokens that could not be claimed.

vestedAmountForSpecificWalletId(address,.notice: Calculates the amount of tokens that has already vested for a particular payment order with id = walletId associated with a particular paymentReceiver.

viewAllPaymentOrders(address,address).notice: see all active payment orders for a paymentClient associated with a particular paymentReceiver
